reviewText: You will not get any new episodes on this DVD.  All of the episodes are previously aired Disney channel episodes of Mickey Mouse Clubhouse. reviewText: I sometimes see people making negative reviews of older MMCH DVDs because they can watch the episodes for "free" on Disney Jr.  It was costing us an extra $40 per month to get our cable companies package that included Disney Jr.  So for us, since this is by far our two year old's favorite show, it makes a lot of sense to cut the cable bill and get the DVDs.  Especially since he tends to watch his favorites over and over.  Now Mickey can go with us to grandma's house, in the car, anywhere there is a DVD player, day or night.  The shows in this one seem to be older episodes, but all very cute and engaging and little man loves them.

reviewText: We bought this for our 2 year old son for Christmas, and he loves it!  It keeps his attention, and he tells me all about each episode when it is done.There are four episodes on the DVD, which makes it an excellent value.  The first episode, Minnie is trying to figure out who took something, while Goofy searches for a missing friend.  The second episode is about Donald, who is a frog looking for a kiss from Daisy.  The third episode is Minnie's take on Little Red Riding Hood as she tries to get soup to a sick Goofy.  The fourth episode is Sleeping Minnie, of course, a spin off on Sleeping Beauty.The stories aren't close enough to the original fairy tales to be boring or repetitive. Of course, Toodles is there, and the format of Mickey Mouse Clubhouse, with all the standard songs, which any little fan will love!The DVD also includes an interactive Toodles game, though my son is too young to play it yet!Definitely worth the money!
